# Nuxt Boilerplate – Project Rules

## Feature-Based Architecture

New features go in `app/features/<name>/` with this structure:
- `components/` – feature-local Vue components
- `composables/` – `useFeature.ts` bridges store ↔ components
- `stores/` – `useFeatureStore.ts` (Pinia setup store)
- `models/` – Pinia ORM entity models
- `types/` – `feature.types.ts`
- `locales/` – `en.json`

Pages are thin wrappers — they delegate to feature components.

## TypeScript

- No `any` — ever
- All params and return types must be explicit
- `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/aliases

## No Comments

Write self-documenting code. No inline comments, no JSDoc.
Absolutely no comments are allowed in the code, not even `// TODO:` comments. No exceptions.

## i18n

- All UI text via `$t()` — never hardcode strings
- `features/<name>/locales/en.json` → accessible as `$t('<name>.key')`
- `app/shared/locales/en.json` → accessible as `$t('key')` globally
- English only

## Pinia

- Setup store style: `defineStore('id', () => { ... })`
- State typed explicitly: `ref<MyType | null>(null)`

## Pinia ORM

- Models in `features/<name>/models/ModelName.ts`
- Use `@Num(0)`, `@Str('')`, `@Bool(false)` decorators
- Access via `useRepo(ModelName)`

## Styling

- `<style lang="scss" scoped>` in every component
- BEM class naming: `.block__element--modifier`
- CSS custom properties from `_variables.scss` — no hardcoded values

## Auto-Imports (never import manually)

Vue reactivity, Nuxt composables, `defineStore`, all composables and stores
from `app/composables/`, `app/stores/`, `app/features/*/composables/`, `app/features/*/stores/`

## Git Commits – Conventional Commits

Format: `type(scope): short description`

Types: `feat` | `fix` | `refactor` | `style` | `docs` | `test` | `chore` | `build` | `ci` | `perf` | `revert`

Scope = affected feature or area: `auth`, `home`, `i18n`, `deps`, `layout`

```
feat(auth): add login page and auth store
fix(home): correct hero subtitle alignment
chore(deps): update nuxt to 4.4.5
refactor(auth): extract login logic into useAuth composable
```

- Subject: max 72 chars, lowercase, no trailing period
- Breaking change: `feat(auth)!: remove legacy session`

## Dependencies

- **Do not delete dependencies:** Only delete a dependency or module if the user explicitly requested it, or if we mutually agreed that it is no longer needed. In case of any errors, it is better to work around or configure the faulty module rather than deleting it without asking.
